title: For Sale/Trade:  **SALE PENDING** S&W 65 3" Pre-Lock .357 MAG
postcontent:
**SALE PENDING** Up for sale or trade is my Smith and Wesson pre-lock model 65-3 with a 3 inch barrel. These 3" K-frames are regarded by many as the perfect concealed carry .357 Magnum. This reputation was gained on behalf of the size, weight, round butt frame, barrel length, fixed combat sights, stainless steel, and full length ejector rod. These M&Ps were one of the last revolvers to see widespread use by Law Enforcement, with the FBI being the most high profile user of these guns. If you intend to carry a .357 IWB, then this is one of the best choices available. For those of you that camp, hike or hunt, the 3" K-frames make for the perfect Florida woods gun.

This particular gun is in excellent overall condition. This is not a beat-to-hell Police trade-in gun. There are some small nicks here and there, which is normal for a revolver this old. The gun has an estimated 500 rounds through it. There is no evidence of flame cutting on the top strap and the forcing cone looks great. This gun comes with the original factory Magna grips.

Several of these S&Ws, in similar condition, recently SOLD (not LISTED) for $700 on Gunbroker. The pre-lock guns have steadily risen in value. They have become highly desirable and their market values have adjusted accordingly. I personally believe these pre-lock S&Ws will continue to rise in value, as Smith and Wesson no longer makes them with this level of parts quality and hand-fitting. Sorry folks, but I won't be trading this one for your Taurus, Ruger, or Grandpa's old single shot. Ridiculous offers that are not even on the same playing field will be ignored. 

**SALE PENDING** Price is $700 FIRM face-to-face in Tampa Bay. Florida Driver's License and CCW required. If no CCW, then a signed Bill of Sale will be required.

title: For Trade:  Czech VZ 58 / BEECHWOOD & Zahal
location: North end near Worthington, Columbus, Ohio
postcontent:
I have one of the very last rifles put together using the original Beechwood furniture that Czechpoint was able to put out. So, that makes it pretty special. I also have done some searching and found the original Bipod and NIGHT SIGHTS that are impossible to come by. Still have original box also.
I think this rifle was number 9 out of 14 (I'm going to call Czechpoint to confirm which number via Serial#). After running out of the Beech, they went to the composite furniture and then the folding metal stock, which is where they are now (sold out though).

In case you think this is just another AK, then you are very wrong. No parts are interchagable and they are VERY different (although they DO look the same). Here are some of the differences:

Short gas piston
Milled receiver, not stamped
About a pound lighter
Hold open cover at the end of the magazine
Can be fed by clip while open
Striker fired (similar to Glock)
Tilting lock action with dropping block (similar to Walther P38, or Beretta 92s)
Aluminum Alloy Magazines

When it is first picked up, it is noticed how well it is balanced. Has been said that it feels like an M14. It will shoot a 123 grain projectile at over 2200 fps. A bit faster and very accurate as hell.

I have it set up right now with the Zahal furniture, which is worth a pretty penny too. Little compartments everywhere and rails upon rails. Nice tactical set up compared to older set up. I can deliver in either configuration. Both are in EXCELLENT condition.
